Caught!
Escape the Noose

by T H Duncan

Now you've gone and done it!

Well, you never actually did it, but John Smith, (you remember Johnny? You kissed his wife, remember?), well he has a grudge against you and so he whispered your name into the Sheriff's ear.

And now, with the Captain's Cup having been stolen from the Lord Commander's quarters, and a willing witness to testify against you, (good old, Johnny), you will be hanged on the morrow until you are dead.

Until then, you are to be a guest at his Lord Commander's prison, situated beyond the drawbridge, beside the moat. If the cells had windows, the views would be striking in the Spring time.....

Get out. I don't know how. Just do something.

They say with innocence comes luck....and you're gonna need plenty of luck.
Castle Black Prison Cell

You are in a damp, dingy, very smelly prison cell. Dirty straw, that has been used for bedding, (and probably the wiping of many bums), litters the cold, stone floor. A wooden bucket, which is the chief source of the smell, lies in the corner and the wet stone walls, that make up your tiny new home, begin to feel very oppressive. A yellow light flickers through the iron bars of your locked prison door, illuminating how small your miserable surroundings really are.

You can see a Hallway west leading from your cell.

> search straw

> search straw

What luck!  After a thorough search amongst  the revolting, smelly straw, you find a rusting iron key. Of course you take it!

> unlock door

> unlock door

You try the clunky iron key in your cell door - "It will never work", you tell yourself as you fumble it in.......then click, clack! The door is now unlocked

> w

> w

Hallway

This Hallway is where a Prison Guard normally sits, in the light, under the low spluttering torch. Normally they would be asleep or singing or biting nails, giving the prisoners verbal abuse, farting, moaning, swearing - but mostly sleeping. Funny, someone should be here.....

There is an empty prison cell opposite the one you frequented, and stairs at the end of the hall.

There is a foul smell coming from near the stairs.

You can go back into your cell, (why? -  I do not know), look into the empty cell, go to the foot of the stairs or investigate the foul smell.

> w

> w

West Prison Cell

Another cell, identical to the one you were thrown in, except this one is cleaner, if that were possible. And yes, another bucket can be found in here too.

You can go east.

> open bucket

> open bucket

You open it.
It contains a flat stone.
> x flat stone

> x flat stone

A rather stinky, slimy, filthy smooth stone. It...it has markings on one side, but you can't make them out in this gloom

> take flat stone

> take flat stone

You now have a smelly stone. Well done.
> e

> e

Hallway

This Hallway is where a Prison Guard normally sits, in the light, under the low spluttering torch. Normally they would be asleep or singing or biting nails, giving the prisoners verbal abuse, farting, moaning, swearing - but mostly sleeping. Funny, someone should be here.....

There is an empty prison cell opposite the one you frequented, and stairs at the end of the hall.

There is a foul smell coming from near the stairs.

You can go back into your cell, (why? -  I do not know), look into the empty cell, go to the foot of the stairs or investigate the foul smell.

> use torch on flat stone

> use torch on flat stone

the markings are clearer. It says, "Third bar loose under mo.....", nothing more than that

> se

> se

Midden Pit

A foul pit where the Guards empty the buckets and trays of scrap food. It is now buzzing with flies and crawling with maggots, and they seem to have eaten all the best bits.

........something catches your eye......it is a knife sticking out of some brown ooze

You can go northwest.

> take knife

> take knife

You take it. You never know, the knife might come in handy.
> nw

> nw

Hallway

This Hallway is where a Prison Guard normally sits, in the light, under the low spluttering torch. Normally they would be asleep or singing or biting nails, giving the prisoners verbal abuse, farting, moaning, swearing - but mostly sleeping. Funny, someone should be here.....

There is an empty prison cell opposite the one you frequented, and stairs at the end of the hall.

There is a foul smell coming from near the stairs.

You can go back into your cell, (why? -  I do not know), look into the empty cell, go to the foot of the stairs or investigate the foul smell.

> sw

> sw

Stairs

Some stone steps, worn in the centre from heavy foot traffic over the many years, lead up, to the West.

The only way out - onwards and upwards!

You can go northeast or west.

> w

> w

The Prison Barracks

A medium sized room now lies before you, with an exit directly across from where you now stand.

The room is lit by a torch, like the one in the Hallway downstairs, but this room is cleaner and smells much better.

There are four beds evenly spaced out and two of those beds are occupied by Prison Guards fast asleep, snoring loudly. One is wearing his uniform, the other is naked....uuurrrghh!

Four, medium sized wooden trunks, lay at the foot of each bed.

You can see far left chest, far right chest, near left chest and near right chest.

You can go east or west.

> open far right chest

> open far right chest

You open it.

This is not a good idea the chests creak too loudly.

It contains trousers.
> take trousers

> take trousers

You take these out of the chest. Maybe a bit short for you?
> wear trousers

> wear trousers

You put these on. Yes, a bit short, but suprisingly comfortable - and warm.

> open near right chest

> open near right chest

You open it.

Are you deaf? Because, I assure you, the Guards are not!

It contains boots and guards jacket.
> take guards jacket

> take guards jacket

you carefully take the jacket. Let's hope it fits....
> wear guards jacket

> wear guards jacket

You put the jacket on. Another layer to keep you warm

> w

> w

A Hallway

This Hallway is well lit with torches blazing away in sconces fixed to the walls at a high level.

There are three closed doors, one at either end of the Hallway and the other half way along its North wall.

Nothing more of note is in sight.

Your stomach makes a growling noise as you immediately identify a missed sensation!......the wondeful smell of......food!

You can go north, west or east.

> n

> n

Kitchen

The smell from this room nearly overpowers you. The breads and the spices and the stewing pots all mix into a wonderful, potent mix. A length of rope holds up a rack of pots and pans and a small thin cupboard stands to one side. At the counter is a portly cook, chopping that lovely food.

You can see a tray.

You can go south.

There at the counter busy at his work is a fat, nearly naked cook. He looks up at you, snarling.....

The cook eyes you up and down, "They sent me a slovely dressed guard? You're useless dressed like that. The Master would skin me alive if you serve. I need an assistant!" moans the chef.

"I can't serve them! I'm not wearing any clothes!" continues the naked chef, as he, very, very carefully, stirs the hot soup.

"Well do something! Either get changed and pick up the tray and take it out to the guards!" shouts the extremely irate cook, waving the meat cleaver at you, "Or go find me an assistant!"

> cut rope

> cut rope

You take out the rusty knife and start sawing the rope.

The cook looks at you quizically. Then he looks up.......

The rope suddenly snaps! and the whole rack with pots and pans comes crashing down on top of the hapless cook.

He is knocked unconcious.

> drop trousers

> drop trousers

You drop it.
> drop guards jacket

> drop guards jacket

You drop it.
> open cupboard

> open cupboard

You open it.
It contains a Cook's hat and apron.
> wear apron

> wear apron

You put on the silly hat and tie the apron around your waist. You now look like the kitchen staff.

> take length of rope

> take length of rope

You take the rope
> drop flat stone

> drop flat stone

You drop it.
> take tray

> take tray

You carefully pick up the tray, trying not to salivate all over it

> eat food

> eat food

You scoff the nearest thing you can get your hands on. You don't have time to identify it. You just cram it in your mouth. What a sensation! That, whatever it was, was lovely!
> s

> s

A Hallway

This Hallway is well lit with torches blazing away in sconces fixed to the walls at a high level.

There are three closed doors, one at either end of the Hallway and the other half way along its North wall.

Nothing more of note is in sight.

Your stomach makes a growling noise as you immediately identify a missed sensation!......the wondeful smell of......food!

You can go north, west or east.

> w

> w

A Dining Hall

This is the largest of the rooms you have been in so far. It has high ceilings and lots of torches around the perimeter.

You can see another exit, to the West, but between you and the door is a long wooden table.

Sat at that table, are two Guards eating some food.

They are too busy devouring their tasty meal to notice you come into the room.

Don't look them in the eye and don't say a word!

Without looking up the Guards shout,

"Hey! Over here boy! Double quick!", waving you over to the table. "Just put it down on the table and clear off"

"'Ere. You 'ad better go and ask the Master what 'e wants for dinner. 'E's in 'is fancy bedroom", says the Redhead.

"But don't let no rat in when you open the fancy door! He's scared stiff of 'em", laughs the other guard.

(You had better disappear, quick, before they recognize you!)

> w

> w

You walk steadily towards the West door, trying not to tremble and wishing they don't call you back

A Hallway 3

This hallway is well lit with a nice thick green carpet running up the centre. Several pictures are strapped to the wall.

An ornate door is to the North, and a plain oak door to the South.

Nothing else of any interest is here.

You can go east (back to where the Guards are eating), north or south.

> s

> s

A Lobby

A small area with a few hooks probably for cloaks or wet gear and a rack for muddy boots.

To the South, through an open doorway is the outside world. So close, and yet so far, as an armed guard can be seen on patrol out there.

You can go south or north.

Something black shoots across your feet

It's a rat!

> catch rat

> catch rat

You scoop the rat into your silly chef's hat and place it on your head - Ratatouille anyone?

> n

> n

A Hallway 3

This hallway is well lit with a nice thick green carpet running up the centre. Several pictures are strapped to the wall.

An ornate door is to the North, and a plain oak door to the South.

Nothing else of any interest is here.

You can go east (back to where the Guards are eating), north or south.

> n

> n

A Master Bedroom

A bedroom the size of 20 prison cells.

High ceilings, carpets and rugs and furs on the floor with many pictures and tapestries hanging from the walls.

A large 4 poster bed adorns the middle of the room. It has ornate curtains tied back with bright yellow rope, big fluffy pillows and cushions.

A large fireplace stands cold, the fire lies built, but unlit.

An oval, glass window lets in natural daylight  onto a ornate writing desk.

You can go south.

A man gets up from behind the desk.  He sneers at you.

It is - The Master.

He is a full head taller than you. He holds something shiny and sharp and sinister in his hands..... ....

"You are no cook!" snarls the Master, "You're that damned thief!"

The Master takes a confident step closer......

> use rat on master

> use rat on master

You take off the silly looking chef's hat and pluck up the rat from your head.

"What is that?", whispers the Matster as you step toward him, "No. No. Wait! Wait!" he stammers as you let the rat dangle by it's tail in front of you. Now it's your turn to sneer.

The Master turns to run but wacks his head on a low shelf and crashes to the ground. He is unconcious.

You gently place the rat on the floor. He shakes his little paw at the Master, salutes you, then scampers back off beneath the gap in the door.

> take letter opener

> take letter opener

You pick up the shiny, sharp blade
> open desk

> open desk

You open it.
it contains a book and a small box.
> read book

> read book

Inside is an index with differing words adjacent each day. The last three entries are;

"Grendel"

"Alibaba"

"Excalibur"

> cut yellow rope

> cut yellow rope

You take your new sharp letter opener and cut the curtain rope down

> open window

> open window

You look out of the window into a sky so blue it hurts your eyes.

The wind in your face feels wonderful. You smile. Then you stop.

You tie together the two lengths of rope, that you aquired and then secured it to the window frame, praying it will hold. You throw the other end out of the window.

Taking one last look back into the Master's bedroom, you slither down the rope........

Through the window

.....It was a good job that last bit of rope was long enough. You slightly twist your ankle but you will be able to run that off.

You look up at the prison walls, stick out your tongue and turn your back on bad food, bad people and bad choices.......

You won! Congratulations!

There are three ways to win. Have you tried them all?

Note your score?  Can you beat it?
